  "prompt": "What should I wear to prom?",
  "response": "Choosing what to wear to prom depends on several factors, including your personal style, the prom theme, and dress code. Here are some tips to help you decide:\n\n### For Women:\n1. **Dress Style**: \n   - Consider a gown or a stylish cocktail dress. Popular styles include A-line, mermaid, ball gown, or fitted styles.\n   - Explore colors and fabrics that make you feel confident. Glamorous options often include sequins, lace, or satin.\n\n2. **Accessories**: \n   - Choose jewelry that complements your outfit, such as earrings, a bracelet, or a clutch purse.\n   - Select shoes that match your dress; consider comfort as you'll be standing and dancing.\n\n3. **Hair and Makeup**: \n   - Decide whether to style your hair up or down, and consider a professional hairstylist if you're looking for something special.\n   - Makeup should enhance your features while matching the overall look.\n\n### For Men:\n1. **Suit or Tuxedo**:\n   - A classic tuxedo is always a great choice, but a well-fitted suit in a color that suits you can also look sharp.\n   - Pay attention to tie or bow tie options\u2014select something that complements your date's outfit if you want a matching look.\n\n2. **Shirt and Accessories**: \n   - Select a shirt that fits well and matches your suit. A white dress shirt is a classic choice.\n   - Accessories like a pocket square or cufflinks can add a touch of personality.\n\n3. **Shoes**: \n   - Opt for polished dress shoes that fit well and match your outfit. Avoid sneakers unless the prom has a very casual vibe.\n\n### General Tips:\n- **Fit and Comfort**: Make sure whatever you choose fits you well and is comfortable, as you\u2019ll wear it for several hours.\n- **Plan Ahead**: If you want to custom/make a dress or suit, start planning early to allow for fitting and alterations.\n- **Budget**: Set a budget for your outfit including accessories, hair, and makeup.\n- **Consult**: If you're going with a date, consider coordinating your outfits to ensure a cohesive look.\n\nUltimately, wear something that makes you feel fabulous and confident! Enjoy your prom!",
